relation: Type: Rose Springs Corner Notched Arrowhead
A highly unusual "lop-sided" translucent diagonally banded duo-flow obsidian Rose
Springs Corner Notched Arrowhead which is well flaked on both faces with very detailed
and intricate flaking patterns to 2 edges. I can't explain the asymmetrical form, other than it
might have been the result of ancient re-working for whatever reason. Quite a nice piece
Era: Developmental to Classic Phase - 600 to 1,600 years old
From the George & Beth Miller collection. The Millers mostly hunted
ancient sites in Modoc County, California, Oregon and Churchill
County, Nevada. From our experience with artifacts from these
areas, we judge this one to be from Lake County, Oregon
